## Gum Command Reference

### Styling
```bash
# Border types: none, normal, rounded, thick, double
gum style --border rounded "Content"

# Colors (foreground)
gum style --foreground 46 "Green text"    # Success
gum style --foreground 196 "Red text"     # Error
gum style --foreground 51 "Blue text"     # Info

# Padding and margins
gum style --padding "1 2" "Padded content"
gum style --margin "1" "With margin"

# Width
gum style --width 60 "Fixed width content"
```

### Input
```bash
# Text input
NAME=$(gum input --placeholder "Your name")

# Password input
PASS=$(gum input --password --placeholder "Password")

# Multiline
TEXT=$(gum write --placeholder "Enter text (Ctrl+D to finish)")
```

### Selection
```bash
# Choose one
OPTION=$(gum choose "Red" "Green" "Blue")

# Choose multiple
SELECTED=$(gum choose --no-limit "A" "B" "C")

# Filter (fuzzy search)
FILE=$(gum filter $(ls))
```

### Confirmation
```bash
# Simple yes/no
gum confirm "Delete file?" && rm file.txt

# With custom text
gum confirm "Continue?" --affirmative "Yes!" --negative "No way"
```

### Progress
```bash
